This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. Janet Morris has written seven science
fiction novels so far. These are grouped into two series, the Solistra series

00:49.460 --> 00:56.860
and the Saga of the Carrion Empire. Morris' novels are characterized by strongly
developed characters and well-drawn backgrounds, and they feature hard science.

00:57.080 --> 01:05.980
The Solistra series consists of four novels, High Couch of Solistra, The Golden
Sword, Wind from the Abyss, and The Carnelian Throne. The protagonist of the

01:05.980 --> 01:13.260
series is Estri, the courtesan who gradually learns more about her real identity
and the power she has inherited. The series, still incomplete, chronicles

01:13.260 --> 01:22.700
Estri's awakening. We asked Morris what she was aiming at when she wrote the
series. I was actually trying to come to terms with the fact that logically and

01:22.700 --> 01:35.100
mathematically I couldn't come to terms with the incidences of ESP that I
experienced in my own life. And some of the more tenuous philosophical

01:35.100 --> 01:45.060
intuitions that I was having that I just couldn't state. There's no other way
really to state those concepts on one level. The relationship of mind to

01:45.060 --> 01:56.380
probability, our connection to time, whether we indeed are co-creators in some
sense of the universe in which we're living and we're making a future in the

01:56.380 --> 02:04.540
past at once. Sometimes in particle physics I begin to wonder if the universe
isn't just giving us whatever particle we choose to dream up. You know, it's

02:04.540 --> 02:12.080
just as soon as we think it up, then it comes into being, because we seem to be
going further and further down, and every time we go down another level, I mean,

02:12.140 --> 02:21.040
the quarks split up into little quarks, and it's endless. And a lot of times you
could come up with a good mathematical reason for something, then maybe the

02:21.040 --> 02:31.360
universe is convinced and it produces it. I have no idea of whether that's going
to turn out to be what it is, but if indeed it is, if the anthropic principle is

02:31.360 --> 02:40.380
anywhere near valid, that it is something like that happening, that we are, in a
sense, central to creation, which would be nice. I mean, it suits my egotism.

02:45.800 --> 02:57.720
Morris had other aims in mind as well. On another level, I wanted to talk about
genetic predispositions, and very bright people have a particular problem with

02:57.720 --> 03:07.680
both human relationships and sexuality, and I wanted to talk about that, because
no matter how intelligent and logical you are, at a certain point you have to

03:07.680 --> 03:18.800
deal with what is your genetic conditioning, and you really get a snootful of it
in a sex act. I mean, a person who is intelligent and monitors what's happening

03:18.800 --> 03:30.300
to them as they become aroused, really realizes that there is a different and
much more primingal person inside each of us. And I had, at that time, I had, at

03:30.300 --> 03:40.340
that time, begun to despair of nurture having anything to do at all with human
behavior, thinking that it was almost everything we do seem to me at that point

03:40.340 --> 03:52.940
in time to be genetically prompted. What Ed Wilson said, that the urge to
creativity might be inextricably linked to the desire to own and dominate, and

03:52.940 --> 04:02.440
that's one of the central themes there. Morris' upbringing also influenced her
writing the series. I was sort of born post-liberated. I was the guy. I was the

04:02.440 --> 04:13.000
oldest child, and I was very intelligent, and I was expected to do all the
things that any young man is supposed to do. So I had come to grips with being a

04:13.000 --> 04:21.400
post-liberated female, and these people were trying to get to where I started
out in agony. These women's livers, not realizing what they were letting

04:21.400 --> 04:35.600
themselves in for, I also wanted to talk about that. And the estuary persona is
a persona that is in no way less than wholly female, while being very

04:35.600 --> 04:43.300
intelligent and reasonably comfortable with that talent. So I wanted to talk a
little. It was an injection at that time that I was putting into consciousness

04:43.300 --> 04:51.920
to sort of inoculate people against extremes of the female liberation movement.
