This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. Science fiction author Janet Morris has
written seven novels so far. Both her series feature female protagonists who are

23:38.120 --> 23:46.320
neither shrinking violets nor female versions of Conan the Barbarian or
Superman. Estry and Shebot are believable characters. They are women with both

23:46.320 --> 23:53.880
strong points and weak points as are most human beings. Morris does not use them
to preach a particular point of view. Morris feels very strongly that women must

23:53.880 --> 24:01.660
be willing to tackle the future head on, be willing to embrace and make use of
technological developments. In fact, she believes these developments will lessen

24:01.660 --> 24:12.300
the importance of physical differences between the sexes. It's a problem for
females in the age that is coming, if indeed it continues to be the case,

24:12.420 --> 24:25.220
because without good technical facility, good math willingness to deal with
computers, they're going to be dinosaurs. And the same instrument, one can be

24:25.220 --> 24:34.480
equal at a computer if one masters the computer. There's a potential for real
equality, an intellectual equality, now that has never existed before, partly

24:34.480 --> 24:44.340
because menial labor and physical strength is no longer a great part of what
makes one a functional human being in a society, and partly because of the

24:44.340 --> 24:54.960
concerns of the society itself. It is not going to happen if women don't start
doing their own work in the areas involved and getting their facility up there.

24:55.220 --> 25:03.680
And if I can do it, the rest of them can do it. There's no reason why anyone
should be in a self-inflicted ghetto.

25:06.760 --> 25:19.320
I'd really like to see ladies spending more time trying to become premier in
their field the way a guy has to. I mean, it's a responsibility that one takes

25:19.320 --> 25:27.360
on very early in life. I am going to be successful at something, specific
besides childbearing. Not that childbearing isn't a nice part of life, but there

25:27.360 --> 25:35.540
definitely is more. Although Morris writes about competent female protagonists,
and she herself is obviously a very capable individual, she does not necessarily

25:35.540 --> 25:44.240
go along with the feminist movement. People assume that I am a feminist, and I
really don't want to be associated with a bunch of ladies standing out in the

25:44.240 --> 25:52.900
middle of the street screaming for their rights. It's just not me. I'm not
comfortable with them. I don't agree with them. I don't like oversimplification.

25:53.200 --> 26:02.120
I don't believe that conditioning is a great part of what makes a person what
they are, that the fact that if you're a little girl and you don't have pockets

26:02.120 --> 26:12.380
in your pants, you're doomed, it's just, I don't believe it. A great degree of
it is genetic inheritance, but one does have control over one's own fate.

26:12.980 --> 26:21.260
Intelligence will go where you point it, and there are plenty of intelligent
women out there. I'd like to see them do something with that intelligence.

26:21.920 --> 26:31.480
Morris is herself, an individual who aspires to achieve and to succeed. She
doesn't look externally for her identity. I've ended up on panels before I knew

26:31.480 --> 26:40.940
better at conventions where I look around me and everyone else in that panel is
a woman, and someone has put me in a ghetto, and invariably they all write

26:40.940 --> 26:50.440
fantasy or they all write very light science fiction, and nobody is writing the
sort of thing that I'm writing, and nobody is interested in talking about what

26:50.440 --> 26:58.100
I'm interested in talking about. I was at one where the moderator said, oh,
isn't this wonderful? We're all ladies. We'll have a consciousness-raising

26:58.100 --> 27:06.920
session, and I just about slid under the table. It's just not my style. It's not
what I'm interested in. It's not what I'm comfortable with, and I don't even

27:06.920 --> 27:18.240
mind if large groups of females want to organize for their rights, although the
Constitution does not guarantee any right except the right to struggle to

27:18.240 --> 27:30.600
succeed. Nobody's given you the right to have anything gratis in America just to
try to get it, but they're not speaking for me. Janet Morris is an outstanding

27:30.600 --> 27:37.380
writer who made her appearance in the late 1970s. The care she puts into her
characters into the science in her science fiction makes her books well worth

27:37.380 --> 27:37.700
reading.

